<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-11-29T21:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-11-29T21:49:00-05:00" n="633" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d633">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.51/438.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Blanchard</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-11-29T22:00:00-04:49">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1915—10 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Recommended in conference with the Admiral that $100,000 out of funds in
                            hand be paid to Haitian Government. The Government has asked for $48,000
                            in the case of the Central Railroad of Haiti, and all will be paid
                            tomorrow. A general modus vivendi is being signed. Think most advisable
                            loan $1,500,000 be arranged immediately after the departure of
                            commission, and so recommend.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>